{"cursor":"4281","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Chaudhary ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|ÚÙØ¯ÙØ±Ù}}}}; {{lang-bn|à¦à§à¦§à§à¦°à§}}; {{lang-\nhi|à¤à¥à¤§à¤°à¥ }})' is a term in Indo-Aryan languages, literally meaning \"holder of\nfour\". Chowdhury (also spelt Chaudri, Choudhury, Choudary, Chaudhari,\nChaudhary, Choudhary, Choudhury, Chaudhury, Chaudhry, Choudhury, Chowdhery,\nChowdhary, Chowdhury, or Choudhry) is a hereditary title of honor, awarded by\nMughal Emperors to persons of eminence or royalty. In some cases it may also\nmean \"power\". Chaudhary word derived from sanskrit word,Chatur Dhrit,meaning\n\"One who holds all the four varnas(groups)of society ie respected by all.This\ntitle was originally for the ruling brahmans in vedic period who were later\nknown as Taga also.Still Chaudhary title is respectfully used for Taga / Tyagi\nBrahmans (Hindu & Muslim)in UP,Haryana& Uttaranchal,Bhumihar Brahmans in Bihar\n& land lord brahmans in Bengal ( chaudhary / raichaudhary).Later on,other caste\ngroups also started having their heads being termed as chaudhary like Chaudhary\nBrahm_Prakash Yadav :- The 1st Chief Minister Of Delhi and a Freedom Fighter.\nCh. Brahm Prakash Yadav played an important role in the Individual Satyagraha\nMovement launched by Mahatma Gandhi in 1940 and was among the leaders of the\nâundergroundâ activities in Delhi during the âQuit Indiaâ movement. He was\nimprisoned many times during the freedom struggle. Mahendra Tikait being the\nchaudhary of Baliyan Khap of Jats.Chaudhary Raghuvir Narayan Singh Tyagi was\nthe Raja of Asaura,Hapur in Uttar Pradesh and married in the family of Maharaja\nof Benaras.\n\nTraditionally, the term is used as a title indicating the ownership of ancestral\nland, but in contemporary usage it is often taken as a surname or title.\n\nDuring the Mughal era, a talukh or district usually consisted of 84 villages\nand a central town. The talukhdar was required to collect taxes, maintain law\nand order, and provide military supplies and manpower to the provincial\ngovernment. In most cases the talukhdar's were entitled to retain 10% of the\ncollected revenue.\n\nHowever, during the Sikh rule in Punjab this title became very common and quite\na few village headmen or \"Lumberdars\" were given \"Chowdhary\" as a title by\nMaharaja Ranjit Singh. Ever since, the Chowdharys of Chakwal style themselves as\n\"Chowdharial\" to distinguish themselves from the newly appointed men.\nIn northern Indian states such as Haryana, Punjab, Rajasthan, the title is used\nby landowning ethnic group and community of Jat, Yadav , Gujjars, Rajputs use\nthis title.\n","linknr":129,"url":"Chaudhary","recorded":1374541670,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Chaudhary&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Chaudhary&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Chaudhary&action=edit","/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing/1","/wiki/Template:Citation_needed","/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability#Burden_of_evidence","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Example.of.complex.text.rendering